{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BaseMaterial3D"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/basematerial3d\/anisotropyflowmap"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Texture that offsets the tangent map for anisotropy calculations and optionally controls the anisotropy effect (if an alpha channel is present). The flowmap texture is expected to be a derivative map, with the red channel representing distortion on the X axis and green channel representing distortion on the Y axis. Values below 0.5 will result in negative distortion, whereas values above 0.5 will result in positive distortion."}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot14BaseMaterial3DC17anisotropyFlowmapAA9Texture2DCSgvp","roleHeading":"Instance Property","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"anisotropyFlowmap","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Texture2D","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot9Texture2DC"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"}],"symbolKind":"property","title":"anisotropyFlowmap","role":"symbol"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"anisotropyFlowmap","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Texture2D","text":"Texture2D","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot9Texture2DC"},{"kind":"text","text":"? { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discus